# Project 04 — Django Hello API

## What I learned
- How to set up a Django project and app
- How Django REST Framework works
- URL routing: root urls.py → app urls.py
- Writing a view with @api_view decorator
- URL parameters with <str:name>

## Tech used
- Python 3.x
- Django 4.x
- Django REST Framework

## Architecture
Request → Django URL router (helloapi/urls.py)
       → App URL router (api/urls.py)
       → View function (api/views.py)
       → DRF Response → JSON

## Endpoints
GET /api/hello/          → {"message": "Hello from Django!"}
GET /api/greet/<name>/   → {"message": "Hello, <name>!"}

## What breaks at 1M users
- runserver is single-threaded → need Gunicorn + Nginx
- SQLite can't handle concurrent writes → PostgreSQL
- No caching → Redis
- No rate limiting → API gateway